How to work with Threads - Option 1

Write a class that extends Thread
Override the run() method in Thread to perform the behavior you want to execute concurrently
Create the object of this Thread class
Invoke start() on the object created above


How to work with Threads - Option 2

Write a class that implements Runnable interface
Override run() method in this class to invoke the behavior you want to execute concurrently
Create the object of this class that implements Runnable
Create a Thread with the object created above
invoke start() on the thread object created above